<h1>Travis Hellstrom</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://travishellstrom.com/now">travishellstrom.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Woodstock
VT
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Everyday Humanitarian and Executive Coach. CEO, Advance Humanity (Certified B Corporation). Chair, Mission Driven Organizations Masters at Marlboro Graduate School.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I help mindful leaders expand their influence and make the world more awesome.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I believe in advancing humanity, pushing the human race forward, and I'm one of those people crazy enough to think they can change the world.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Anyone can change the world, I learned that in Peace Corps. Live simply.  Choose yourself. Do something amazing.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
"Life is Good The Book" by Bert and John Jacobs
</p>

